  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across most operating conditions. Full 13-factor assessment completed. Decision: Accepted. NOTE: the intermediate validation result at partial-load operating point characterizes inherent variability qualitatively rather than through a structured UQ node, leaving aleatory uncertainty uncharacterized in that result object.",
