      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Partial-load operating point hemolysis validation (3 L/min, 3000 RPM)",
      "description": "CFD hemolysis index compared against bench measurements at reduced-flow VAD operating point. Inherent variability in RBC fragility at low shear rates was assessed qualitatively by the analysis team based on literature ranges; no structured Monte Carlo or interval-arithmetic UQ node was constructed for this operating condition. Predicted HI = 0.0028; measured HI = 0.0031. Qualitative judgment indicates variability is small relative to the acceptance threshold, but the aleatory uncertainty is not formally bounded in this result."
